models.description: The latest GPT-4 Turbo model with vision capabilities. Vision requests can now use JSON mode and function calling. Currently points to gpt-4-turbo-2024-04-09.
GPT-4 Turbo with Vision model. Vision requests can now use JSON mode and function calling. gpt-4-turbo currently points to this version.
GPT-4 Turbo preview model. Currently points to gpt-4-0125-preview.
GPT-4 Turbo preview model intended to reduce cases of “laziness” where the model doesn’t complete a task. Returns a maximum of 4,096 output tokens. Learn more.
GPT-4 Turbo preview model featuring improved instruction following, JSON mode, reproducible outputs, parallel function calling, and more. Returns a maximum of 4,096 output tokens.

GPT-4 model with the ability to understand images, in addition to all other GPT-4 Turbo capabilities. This is a preview model, we recommend developers to now use gpt-4-turbo which includes vision capabilities. Currently points to gpt-4-1106-vision-preview.

GPT-4 model with the ability to understand images, in addition to all other GPT-4 Turbo capabilities. This is a preview model, we recommend developers to now use gpt-4-turbo which includes vision capabilities. Returns a maximum of 4,096 output tokens. Learn more.
Currently points to gpt-4-0613. See continuous model upgrades.
Snapshot of gpt-4 from June 13th 2023 with improved function calling support.
Currently points to gpt-4-32k-0613. See continuous model upgrades. This model was never rolled out widely in favor of GPT-4 Turbo.
Snapshot of gpt-4-32k from June 13th 2023 with improved function calling support. This model was never rolled out widely in favor of GPT-4 Turbo.

New Updated GPT 3.5 Turbo. The latest GPT-3.5 Turbo model with higher accuracy at responding in requested formats and a fix for a bug which caused a text encoding issue for non-English language function calls. Returns a maximum of 4,096 output tokens.
GPT-3.5 Turbo model with improved instruction following, JSON mode, reproducible outputs, parallel function calling, and more. Returns a maximum of 4,096 output tokens.
Similar capabilities as GPT-3 era models. Compatible with legacy Completions endpoint and not Chat Completions.
Legacy Snapshot of gpt-3.5-turbo from June 13th 2023. Will be deprecated on June 13, 2024.
Legacy Snapshot of gpt-3.5-16k-turbo from June 13th 2023. Will be deprecated on June 13, 2024.
